From a0f7728d63e43d693e3aae6a23ab5efdf421f50a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Geoff <geoff.radian6@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 18:44:13 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: add ComputeClass-aware provisioning for GKE Custom
 Compute Classes

This introduces support for referencing GKE Custom Compute Class (CCC)
resources from GCENodeClass, allowing Karpenter to use ComputeClass
priority rules when selecting instance types. This combines Karpenter's
superior lifecycle management (consolidation, drift detection, TTL) with
GKE's native priority-based machine selection semantics.

Key changes:
- Add ComputeClassRef field to GCENodeClassSpec
- New computeclass provider package with priority resolution and filtering
- Priority-aware instance type reordering in CloudProvider pipeline
- ComputeClass name annotation on provisioned NodeClaims
- Graceful degradation when ComputeClass is absent or unreadable
- Functional options pattern for enabling the feature
- Unit tests for priority matching, filtering, and reordering
- Example manifests for cost-optimized and GPU workload patterns

This feature is designed to be gated behind a feature flag
(ComputeClassAwareProvisioning) and requires GKE 1.33.3+ where
ComputeClass is independent of NAP.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
